50|$|Budgeted net {{interest}} on the public debt was approximately $245 billion in FY2012 (7% of spending). During FY2012, the government also accrued a non-cash interest expense of $187 billion for intra-governmental debt, primarily the <b>Social</b> <b>Security</b> <b>Trust</b> <b>Fund,</b> for a total interest expense of $432 billion. This accrued interest {{is added to the}} <b>Social</b> <b>Security</b> <b>Trust</b> <b>Fund</b> and therefore the national debt each year and will be paid to Social Security recipients in the future. However, since it is a non-cash expense it is excluded from the budget deficit calculation.|$|E
